    body_en:
      "**Wider source window â denser briefings.** The nightly cron `cron-video-roundup-background` used to pull only videos with `published_date = yesterday` for each roundup, which made for thin briefings on slow news days (especially per-topic, where 1-2 transcribed videos in a 24 h window is common). The roundup is still KEYED to `roundup_date = yesterday` (the unique constraint stays valid), but `generateVideoRoundup` now pulls source material from a **48 h window** ending at end-of-day yesterday, i.e. `published_date IN [day-before-yesterday, yesterday]` inclusive. New `WINDOW_DAYS = 2` constant in `src/lib/generate-video-roundup.ts`.\n\n**`getVideoTranscriptionsForRoundup` signature widened.** Now takes `(topicId, fromDate, toDate, lang)` â pass the same value for both bounds for the legacy single-day behaviour. Range is inclusive on both sides on `published_date`.\n\n**SSR `/r/` page rebuilt around `video_ids`.** Critical fix that ships with the window widening: the page used to fetch by `(topicId, roundup_date, lang)` and re-sort by `roundup.video_ids`. With a 48 h window, video_ids now contains rows from `roundup_date - 1`, which a single-day fetch silently drops. The page now calls a new `getVideoTranscriptionsByIds(roundup.video_ids, lang)` helper that hydrates the EXACT id list â faithful to whatever window the generator used at write-time. Per-video card links + JSON-LD ItemList URLs use `v.published_date` (with `roundup_date` fallback) instead of the roundup_date so they keep pointing at the real `/v/{date}/{slug}` SSR pages.\n\n**Section copy.** ÂŦ Les vidÃĐos du jour Âŧ / ÂŦ Today's videos Âŧ â **ÂŦ VidÃĐos couvertes Âŧ / ÂŦ Videos covered Âŧ** to reflect that the cards are no longer all from the same calendar day.\n\n**Backward compat.** Old roundups (`video_ids` only spans 1 day) render identically â fetching by IDs returns the same set as the old single-day fetch did. To regenerate any existing roundup with the wider 48 h window: `POST /api/roundups/generate { topicId, date, lang }` (the cron stays skip-if-exists).\n\n**Release.** Bump 2.4.0 â 2.4.1 via `npm run release:patch`. No migration to run.",
