    body_en:
      "**New briefing format.** The per-topic-per-day video roundup at `/{topic}/r/{date}/{slug}` (rendered from `video_roundups.intro_md`) used to be a single one-paragraph intro of 3-5 sentences â too thin for an editorial product. It's now a structured **8-bullet briefing**, each bullet with:\n\n- A **journalistic title** (3-8 words, anchored on a proper noun, product or key figure â e.g. \"GPT-5 jumps to 2M tokens\")\n- A **body of 3-5 sentences** (target 4) with **bold** for proper nouns / numbers / dates, written in dense editorial press style. Never references the source videos / channels / speakers â pure subject-first journalism.\n- 8 distinct angles, no redundancy.\n\nStored as a sequence of `### Title\\n\\nbody...` Markdown in the existing `video_roundups.intro_md` column (no schema change for the roundup itself), rendered with a custom `h3` style (gold, 17px, tight to body) on the SSR page. Added a small \"Briefing\" kicker above the box so the new structure is visually labelled.\n\n**SEO tightened.** The prompt now bans generic phrasing in `seo_title` (\"Daily tech briefing\"), enforces 5-7 specific kebab-case keywords in `slug_keywords` (forbidden words: `news`, `briefing`, `daily`, `ai`, `tech`, `video`, `today`), and demands the `seo_description` contain âĨ 3 specific terms (product names, figures, companies). Concrete examples baked in for both EN + FR (\"Sora 2 vs Veo 3: OpenAI strikes back with native camera mode\" / \"GPT-5 passe Ã  2M de contexte, Anthropic rÃĐplique avec Claude 4.6\").\n\n**Best model in town.** `gpt-4.1-mini` â **`gpt-5.3-chat-latest`** (same model the `/api/news/top-summary` endpoint already uses for top-50 summaries). The roundup is the editorial flagship and the cron is a Netlify background function (15 min budget) so latency is irrelevant; quality is everything. `OPENAI_TIMEOUT_MS` bumped 25s â **60s** to fit the slower (but smarter) model comfortably.\n\n**summary_bullets mirror.** Migration **018** adds `summary_bullets.video_roundup_id INT REFERENCES video_roundups(id) ON DELETE CASCADE` (+ index). On every roundup write the 8 bullets are also persisted as 8 rows in `summary_bullets` with `source_type = 'video_roundup'`, `text = '**Title**\\n\\nBody'`, `bullet_index = 0..7`. This is the same pattern already used for `article` / `video` / `top50` source types â bullets become uniformly queryable across all surfaces (e.g. for future cross-source search, RSS feeds, entity extraction). Failure to write the bullets is non-fatal: the roundup page reads `intro_md`, not these mirror rows.\n\n**Backward compat.** Old single-paragraph roundups already in the DB still render correctly (no `###` headings â ReactMarkdown just renders a paragraph). To regenerate one to the new format: `POST /api/roundups/generate { topicId, date, lang }` (the cron is intentionally skip-if-exists).\n\n**Release.** Bump 2.3.1 â 2.4.0 via `npm run release:minor`. **Run migration 018 in Supabase before the next cron tick** â otherwise the `summary_bullets` insert silently warns and the roundup page is unaffected.",
